ren zu Staat und Gesellschaft im Laufe des 20. Jahrhunderts. Die literarische Moderne spiegelt diesen Wandel in Auseinandersetzungen mit markanten juristischen Fragestellungen wider. Das deutet sich auch in Texten bedeutender älterer Schriftsteller an.  aThis work compiles twelve essays on the complex relationship between the law and literature as viewed from each discipline. It reveals a profound transformation in the relationship of authors to the state and society over the course of the 20th century. Modern literature reflects this change in conflicted portrayals of major juridical issues. These conflicts are also apparent in texts by important writers from earlier periods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCrime in literature. 0aCriminals in literature. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aLaw and literature. 0aLaw in literature. 0aLaw. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2016z9783110485202oZDB-23-DGC0 cEPUBz97831104748550 cprintz978311047362940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047585240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110475852423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110475852.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016